Package: GLLAMMR
Type: Package
Title: Generalized Linear Latent and Mixed Models
Version: 1.0.0
Date: 2026-02-06
Authors@R: c(
    person("Josh", "", email = "your.email@example.com", role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("Claude", "Sonnet 4.5", role = "ctb", comment = "Implementation assistant"))
Description: Comprehensive implementation of Generalized Linear Latent and Mixed
    Models (GLLAMM) following the Stata GLLAMM framework by Rabe-Hesketh, Skrondal,
    and Pickles. Supports multilevel generalized linear models (GLMMs) with Gaussian,
    binomial, Poisson, ordinal, and multinomial responses; factor models; item response
    theory (IRT) models including dichotomous (Rasch, 2PL, 3PL) and polytomous (GRM,
    PCM, GPCM, NRM) models; differential item functioning (DIF) analysis; explanatory
    IRT (EIRT) with item covariates for both dichotomous and polytomous models; latent
    class analysis; structural equation models; mixed response models; and survival
    models. Uses Template Model Builder (TMB) for efficient computation via automatic
    differentiation. Provides comprehensive diagnostics, visualization, and model
    comparison tools.
